-- United Hedged 37 Percent of Second-Quarter Jet Fuel Needs
-- B y   M a r i o   P a r k e r
-- 2012-04-26T20:53:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/united-hedged-37-percent-of-second-quarter-jet-fuel-needs.html
United Continental Holdings Inc. (UAL) 
hedged 37 percent of its jet-fuel requirements for the second
quarter of 2012.  The Chicago-based carrier said on a conference call today
that it locked in its needs at an average Gulf Coast jet fuel
equivalent of $3.18 a gallon and that 36 percent of its expected
fuel consumption for the second half of the year is hedged.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mario Parker in Chicago at 
